 individual securities for our private clients for each asset category we offer a series of fgp pooled funds specifically designed for taxexempt private accounts such as rrsps rrifs and another series designed for taxable private accounts  while these pooled funds are similar to mutual funds they do not require prospectuses and are therefore considered private offerings available to our clients only subject to meeting certain minimum investment requirements  top  foyston gordon  payne inc built by pixelcarve foyston  sub advisory foyston  sub advisory search hide en  fr menu areas of expertise  sub advisory sub advisory access our expertise through partnerships we have created partnerships with a number of investment companies who want their individual investors to have access to top institutional money managers individual investors who may not have access to the account minimums to invest privately with us can access our expertise at much lower minimums ranging from  for mutual fund investing to  or more for separatelymanaged account programs we act as subadvisor for a number of separatelymanaged account programs also known as wrap programs mutual funds and one pooled fund wrap program each subadvisory relationship is treated as a direct institutional client with our investment management customized to meet the needs of program sponsors and their clients our portfolio managers and research teams manage our subadvisory portfolios our client service professionals are also actively involved in the investment process to ensure that program sponsors always receive timely and accurate information    sma wrap programs top  foyston gordon  payne inc built by pixelcarve foyston  firm history foyston  firm history search hide en  fr menu about us  firm history firm history three partners – donald foyston peter gordon and malcolm payne – launched foyston gordon  payne fgp in   each partner brought extensive expertise and experience to the firm – with deep knowledge of the institutional investment and private money management business with a belief in the discipline and success of value style investing fgp soon developed strong connections with clients based on trust and integrity – backed by disciplined research and analysis of the quality and value of potential investments more than three decades later our firm has grown to over  employees while continuing to invest in highquality companies with attractive valuations – just as our original partners did while our firm is supported by an equity interest from affiliated managers group’s amg fgp remains a completely autonomous business in fact almost  percent of fgp is owned by its employees firmly aligning our interests with those of our clients just as our investment team manages portfolios for our institutional and private clients we also participate in the management of our own company when our clients do well we do well – and our history of collective success speaks to the power of disciplined excellence that has always set us apart chairmans message top  foyston gordon  payne inc built by pixelcarve foyston gordon amg  affiliated managers group inc go home news usa websitesasiaaustraliacanadaeuropemiddle eastusa about amgamg overviewphilosophyhistoryclientsproductsamg fundsamg wealth partnersaffiliatesmanagement teamproductsproducts overviewclient typesnew investmentspartnership approachwhy partnership worksinvestment structureinvestor relationsinvestor overviewpublic filings  other financial informationpress releasesannual reportanalyst coverageshareholder informationstock informationcorporate governancemanagement teamboard of directorsinvestor presentationcontact us about amg  amg overviewphilosophyhistoryclientsproductsamg fundsamg wealth partnersaffiliatesmanagement team back to amg affiliatesfoyston gordon  payne incinvestment disciplinefoyston gordon  payne inc “fgp” is a valuestyle investment management firm whose philosophy is based on its view that earnings always matter  fgp believes that high quality sustainable earnings should contribute to producing excellent longerterm valueadded results  the firm’s portfolio managers and analysts use a strict discipline to ensure they do not overpay for earnings  valuation is the key focus and is the primary determinant of the excellent long term results provided to fgp’s clientsfgp’s research analysts form the core of the firm’s research and analysis the analysts’ focus is to generate new investment ideas by putting stocks and bonds through screens for value characteristics quality attributes and recent price changes they also keep a close eye on securities already in the portfoliothe portfolio managers make the final decisions on new additions to the portfolios they manage they look for input and constructive criticism from their analysts and the investment committee and weigh that input before making a final decision within the portfolio the portfolio managers use a model weighting system that takes into consideration input from the analysts in addition to their own judgment of each security’s best overall value in the portfoliothe firmthree partners launched fgp in  to provide portfolio management services to organizations and high net worth individuals more than three decades later the firm continues to invest in what its investment professionals believe are high quality companies with attractive valuations – just like the original partners didfgp is led by its executive committee consisting of bryan pilsworth president  portfolio manager  canadian equities mark thompson chief operating officer and john berry senior vice president  portfolio manager  canadian equitiescontact information adelaide street east suite toronto on canada mc v  wwwfoystoncom site mapcontact uslegal information   affiliated managers group inc all rights reserved foyston gordon  payne inc private company information  bloomberg july    am et capital markets company overview of foyston gordon  payne inc snapshot people company overview foyston gordon  payne inc is a privately owned investment manager the firm provides advisory services to individuals typically high net worth individuals it also manages accounts for pension and profit sharing plans foundations endowments pooled investment vehicles charitable organizations corporations and state or municipal government entities the firm launches and manages equity fixed income and balanced mutual funds for its clients it invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe the firm conducts inhouse research to make its investments it was founded in  and is based in toronto canada with an additional office in montreal canada foyston foyston gordon  payne inc is a privately owned investment manager the firm provides advisory services to individuals typically high net worth individuals it also manages accounts for pension and profit sharing plans foundations endowments pooled investment vehicles charitable organizations corporations and state or municipal government entities the firm launches and manages equity fixed income and balanced mutual funds for its clients it invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe the firm conducts inhouse research to make its investments it was founded in  and is based in toronto canada with an additional office in montreal canada foyston gordon  payne operates as a subsidiary of amg canada corp detailed description  adelaide street eastsuite toronto on mc vcanadafounded in  phone  fax  wwwfoystoncom key executives for foyston gordon  payne inc mr bryan wilfrid pilsworth cfa mba president and portfolio manager of canadian equities mr mark edward thompson chief operating officer and chief compliance officer mr stephen paul copeland cfa cfp senior vice president of investments mr robert james head senior vice president and portfolio manager of fixed income investments mr john charles berry cfa senior vice president and portfolio manager of canadian equities comp